Titolo: Quartet (video game)

Anno: 1986

Descrizione: Quartet (カルテット) is a run-and-gun shooter video game released by Sega for arcades in 1986. Quartet allows one to four players to guide a set of characters through a base taken over by an army of robots. Players control either Joe (yellow), Mary (red), Lee (blue), or Edgar (green) across a number of side-scrolling levels.  The object of the game is to advance through the level, fighting opponents that come out of portals in the walls, and eventually defeat a boss that carries the door key used to open the "exit door" for the level.The game was ported to the Master System, Commodore 64, Amstrad CPC, and ZX Spectrum.

